		QuadraticSolver
	An application to solve quadratic equations. The user inputs the 3 coefficients which should be positive 
numbers. The application outputs the real roots of the equation, if any exist. If the roots are imaginary or outside the 
range of a float type, the user is notified. 
	Unit tests for the entire application are in the /src/Main folder.
	All source code is in the src file.
	Specific unit test are in the same foder as the module they test.
	Licenses are in the folder containing this readme.

		System Requirements
	This application requirs a GNU Linux operating system such as Ubuntu or Mint. This application runs from a command line interface.

		Running the Quadratic solver
	To run the solver, navigate to the folder in which you unzipped the tar file containing the Quad Solver application and type the command 
$ ./QuadSolver.

		Maintenance 
	No future releases are planned.

